{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyView"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color","text":"Color","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore5ColorV"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"tint","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The tint "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to apply."}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this method to override the default accent color for this view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Unlike an app’s accent color, which can be overridden by user"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"preference, the tint color is always respected and should be used as a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"way to provide additional meaning to the control."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This example shows Answer and Decline buttons with ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/green","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/red","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" tint colors, respectively.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct ControlTint: View {","    var body: some View {","        HStack {","            Button {","                \/\/ Answer the call","            } label: {","                Label(\"Answer\", systemImage: \"phone\")","            }","            .tint(.green)","            Button {","                \/\/ Decline the call","            } label: {","                Label(\"Decline\", systemImage: \"phone.down\")","            }","            .tint(.red)","        }","        .buttonStyle(.borderedProminent)","        .padding()","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some controls adapt to the tint color differently based on their style,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the current platform, and the surrounding context. For example, in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS, a button with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PrimitiveButtonStyle\/bordered"},{"type":"text","text":" style doesn’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tint its background, but one with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PrimitiveButtonStyle\/borderedProminent"},{"type":"text","text":" style does. In macOS, neither"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of these button styles tint their label, but they do in other platforms."}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/AnyView\/tint(_:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets the tint color within this view."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLan